    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a memorandum to the Secretary dated August 17, <persName
                        corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> stated that General <persName
                        corresp="#p_COLLINSJL1">Collins</persName> would be briefing the Secretary
                    on the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> “New Approach” studies on August
                    19. <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> enclosed copies of
                    the Joint Chiefs of Staff letter to the Secretary of Defense, June 11, and the
                    Appendix thereto entitled “Present Status of Arrangements With Foreign Countries
                    Relating to the Use of Atomic Weapons” (neither printed), and summarized the
                    contents of both documents in a brief paragraph. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> added his preliminary opinion
                    that “we will have to make an all-out effort to accomplish as much of this
                    program as we can without jeopardizing the political ties which make <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> a major deterrent to Soviet aggression”. The
                    same day, <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> sent a
                    memorandum to the Under Secretary, the Deputy Under Secretary, <persName
                        corresp="#p_BOWIERR1">Bowie</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1"
                        >Smith</persName> of <gloss target="#t_SAE1">S/AE</gloss>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1">MacArthur</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_BYROADEHA1">Byroade</persName> of <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                        >NEA</gloss>, and <persName corresp="#p_PALMERJII1">Palmer</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_WOLFJJ1">Wolf</persName> of <gloss target="#t_RA1"
                        >RA</gloss> informing them that they had also been invited to attend the
                    restricted briefing given to the Secretary by General <persName
                        corresp="#p_COLLINSJL1">Collins</persName> on the morning of August 19. No
                    record of General <persName corresp="#p_COLLINSJL1">Collins</persName>’ briefing
                    has been found in Department of State files. The <persName
                        corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> memoranda to the Secretary and
                    to the Under Secretary, <hi rend="italic">et al</hi>. are in file 740.5/8–1654
                    and 8/1754.</p>
